aspects of the firms operations including fixed income, currency,
commodity and equity portfolios. Prior to Cornerstone, Mr. Eckstein was a
researcher for Luck Trading Company, a commodity trading adviser. Mr. Eckstein
is a co-author of Commodity Investing (John Wiley & Sons, 2008) and is a
frequent speaker at industry events. He holds a Bachelor of Science from Brown
University and a Masters in Public Administration (International Economic
Policy) from Columbia University.Bryan Novak, Senior Managing Director
